{"type":"message","id":"062a80d5","parentId":"14d06f41","timestamp":"2026-03-28T21:29:20.206Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 21 tests pass. Here's a summary of what changed:\n\n### Changes made to `classifier-service.ts`\n\n**1. Trimmed the hard-deny list** — removed ~15 overly aggressive patterns:\n- `rm *`, `rm -f *`, `rm -r *`, `rm -rf *` → only deny `rm -rf /` and `rm -rf /*` (nuking root)\n- `kill -9 *`, `killall *` → removed (legitimate dev ops)\n- `sed -i *` → removed (legitimate file editing)\n- `crontab *` → removed\n- `dd *` → narrowed to `dd if=* of=/dev/*` (only deny actual device writes)\n- `wget -O- *` → removed (harmless download)\n\n**2. Fixed `allSubcommandsAllowed`** — was using the full `candidates` array (which includes synthetic path-stripped/env-stripped variants) as subcommands to check. Now re-splits the actual command string directly, so `find . | grep foo` correctly resolves to `['find .', 'grep foo']` both of which hit built-in allow patterns.\n\n**3. Raised auto-pause thresholds** — from `3 consecutive / 20 total` → `10 consecutive / 50 total`. The old thresholds were hair-trigger for any session doing real work."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":326,"cacheRead":49559,"cacheWrite":1555,"totalTokens":51441,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.00489,"cacheRead":0.0148677,"cacheWrite":0.0058312500000000005,"total":0.02559195}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774733351085}}
